{{> _header title="Typography" navigation=navigation }}
<p>
	As a timeless, highly effective font, Helvetica is at the forefront of the Fandom brand and used across our mobile
	and desktop site and is available in various weights. Our native apps inherit the respective default fonts —
	San Francisco on iOS and Roboto on Android — and also contain various weights.
</p>
<p>
	Note: the 10px size should be displayed in all caps only to ensure proper readability.
</p>
<p>
	In order to use Design System Typography, you need to import <code>/base/_typography.scss</code>
	partial in your SCSS file. It's recommended to use available typography variables
	to keep consistency across products.
</p>

<section>
	<h2 id="font-family">Font Family</h2>
	<p>For highest browser compatibility we decided to follow direction described in <a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2015/11/using-system-ui-fonts-practical-guide/">Using System UI Fonts In Web Design: A Quick Practical Guide</a>. It provides a list of font-families for browsers to fallback. We listed font-families supported by major operating systems and finally we fall back to <code>sans-serif</code>. This way we can avoid web-font delivery process which would hit page performance.</p>
	<code><span class="format-code">$font-family</span>: 'San Francisco', 'Helvetica Neue', 'Roboto', 'Segoe UI', 'Ubuntu', 'Droid Sans', sans-serif;</code>
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="line-height">Line height</h2>
	<code><span class="format-code">$line-height</span>: 1.5em;</code>
</section>

